A Mastery Heatmap visualizes topic-wise performance so users instantly see strengths vs weak areas.
Since you already have topic extraction + quiz analytics, the heatmap is mainly data modeling â†’ scoring â†’ visualization.

1ï¸âƒ£ Define the Data Model (Backend)

You need a persistent structure storing topic attempts + accuracy.

Minimal schema
{
  "user_id": "u1",
  "project_id": "data_science",
  "topics": {
    "Data Mining": {
      "attempted": 32,
      "correct": 24,
      "accuracy": 75,
      "last_attempt": "2026-02-26T12:20"
    },
    "Clustering": {
      "attempted": 18,
      "correct": 6,
      "accuracy": 33
    }
  }
}
How to update after quiz
def update_topic_stats(stats, topic, correct):
    if topic not in stats:
        stats[topic] = {"attempted": 0, "correct": 0}

    stats[topic]["attempted"] += 1
    if correct:
        stats[topic]["correct"] += 1

    stats[topic]["accuracy"] = round(
        stats[topic]["correct"] / stats[topic]["attempted"] * 100
    )

